{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φῐλόλογ-ος</b>, ον, <br /> <b>fond of words, talkative,</b> οἶνος φιλολόγους ποιεῖ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 284 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; φ. καὶ πολύλογος, opposed to βραχύλογος, of Athens, opposed to Sparta, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 641e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>fond of speaking,</b> of Socrates, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Phdr.” 236e. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>fond of dialectic, fond of philosophical argument,</b> opposed to μισόλογος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “La.” 188c; φ. γ᾽ εἶ καὶ χρηστός [prev. author] “Tht.” 161a; ὁ φιλόσοφός τε καὶ ὁ φ. [prev. author] “R.” 582e, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Gnomologium Vaticanum - Kleine Schriften” 74, 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ παρρησίας” p.48 O. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>fond of learning and literature, literary,</b> Λακεδαιμόνιοι.. ἥκιστα φ. ὄντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1398b14; φύσει Ἀθηναῖοι φ. 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 2.3.7: opposed to λογόφιλος(lover of reason), 4th-3rd c.BC: Zeno Citieus Stoicus 1.67; φιλολόγῳ ὑποκατακλίνεσθαι φιλομαθῆ 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.618e, compare 419d\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ἀπαίδευτος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 4.22.107: opposed to πολιτικός, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Lucullus” 42. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>student, scholar,</b> first used by Eratosthenes of himself, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Suetonius Grammaticus et Historicus Latinus “Grammars” 10, compare 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 14.5.15, 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 25, 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 2.4.1, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “Libr.Propr.Prooem.”: but φιλόλογος ὁ φιλῶν λόγους καὶ σπουδάζων περὶ παιδείαν· οἱ δὲ νῦν ἐπὶ τοῦ ἐμπείρου τιθέασιν, οὐκ ὀρθῶς 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista 371. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> of books, <b>learned,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Epistulae ad Atticum” 13.12.3 (_comparative_)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: <b>suitable for a literary man, connected with learning,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 15.15.2. \">Refs</a>] <i>adverb</i> <b>-λόγως</b> <b>learnedly,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 4.11, argument 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ra.” \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> φ. <b>multa,</b> much <b>learned conversation,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Epistulae ad Atticum” 13.52.2. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>studious of words,</b> opposed to φιλόσοφος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus cited in 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “Vita Plotini” 14, etap. 5th c.AD: Proclus Philosophus “in Platonis Timaeum commentarii” 1.86 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator, etc. (Freq. written _paroxytone_ φιλολόγος\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] in codices, as [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 161a (codex B), “Etymologicum Magnum” 406.10: but φιλόλογος Hdn.Gr. 1.233 (from λόγος, not λέγω).) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5378","accentedUnicode":"Φιλόλογος","shortDef":"Philologus, \"lover of words [education]\"","mediumDef":"A man living at the time of the New Testament, only mentioned at Rom.16.15 <BR> § Philologus, \"lover of words [education]\" <br /><b>Philologus,</b> (Proper name), <ref='Rom.16.15'>Rom. 16:15</ref>*","stepGloss":"Philologus","stepTransliteration":"filologos","count":1,"_es_Definition":"Filólogo (ROM.16:15)","_zh_tw_Definition":"非羅羅古 这个陽性專有名詞 人名在原文的意思是 愛字者<br>保羅在羅馬書中問候的一名基督徒  #羅 16:15|","_zh_Definition":"非罗罗古 这个阳性专有名词 人名在原文的意思是 爱字者<br>保罗在罗马书中问候的一名基督徒  #罗 16:15|","_step_Type":"man","_step_Link":"Philologus@Rom.16.15","_vi_Definition":"Phi-lô-lô-gu; Phi-lô-lô-gơ, « người yêu của các từ [giáo dục]».","_zh_tw_Gloss":"非羅羅古","_es_Gloss":"Filólogo","_zh_Gloss":"非罗罗古"}]}